President Trump and Prime Minister Abe of Japan held a press conference at Mar-a-Lago in Florida, discussing their close relationship and the progress made in discussions on North Korea, military issues, and trade. They expressed hope for a successful meeting between President Trump and Kim Jong-un, with President Trump stating that the North Korea problem must be addressed. They also mentioned their coordination with South Korea and the ongoing negotiations for a new trade deal. President Trump thanked President Xi of China for his support and expressed his commitment to addressing the issue of abductions in the upcoming U.S.-North Korea summit. The press conference concluded with President Trump stating that the location for the summit has not been decided yet.